      • reversePath

        public static java.lang.String reversePath(java.lang.Class clazz,
                           java.lang.String propertyPath)
        20100930 I started this to use for reversing from TreeNode to get path to top/root this wont work, unless the parent nodes are also used Take a property path that is "to" a class, and reverse it. Example: from a X class, the propPath "dept.manager.address.zipCode" where address.class would be the clazz; would return "manager.dept", used to get from an address to the dept.
        Parameters:
        clazz -
        propertyPath -
        Returns:
